      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CHEEKY CHEESE (1) filled a minor placing last start at this track behind Flamin' Joe (19.37) in a Grade 5. Settled off speed and worked to the line nicely. Goes very well from this draw with three wins and two minor placings from seven starts. Rates highly and will give a great sight. GOLDEN BLEND (2) turned spotting a big start finishing fourth (18.60) last time in a Grade 5 at Richmond. Has a good record at this journey. Safe beginner who has drawn to advantage. Worth another chance. JET'S DIGGER (8) drawn the outside box and could get a clear run. Was below best last time when 7th and beaten 12 lengths at Richmond (19.25). Has never missed the frame here at the trip including zero wins. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from an outside draw. Can do much better this time. ACE IS FIRE (6) warrants respect although new to this track.",
